[start section id="20101"]

Dr. Jean B. Simmons; Colin English, RPA-C.

[end section id="20101"]

[start section id="20103"]

This is a 58-year-old female with biopsy-proven right colon cancer.  This was found during an evaluation for anemia.  Outside CT that has been read here shows cecal carcinoma with mildly prominent ileocolic mesenteric lymph node.  Otherwise, she is doing well.  She is on iron supplementation.  Her current hemoglobin is 10.3.  CEA is 2.1.  She does have a history of COPD and a phrenic nerve damaged from a left rotator cuff surgery.  Otherwise, healthy.

[end section id="20103"]


